OL,3,CWhy did the mental health care for
OL,4,Ckiller Valdo Calocane go so wrong?
OL,6,F"The same litany of faults is repeated
OL,7,Fagain and again, it's not just simply
OL,8,Fa lack of resources, it's also an
OL,9,Fideological belief that anyone,
OL,10,Fhowever disturbed they may be can be
OL,11,Flooked after in the community,
OL,12,Fparticularly with the community teams
OL,13,Fbeing so overstretched."
OL,15,F'Where are the rights of the families?
OL,16,FWhere are the rights of the public?'
