OL,3,CWhy did the mental health care for
OL,4,Ckiller Valdo Calocane go so wrong?
OL,6,FShe says it 'defies common sense' that
OL,7,Fthis was a man who had been sectioned
OL,8,Ffour times, yet was discharged far too
OL,9,Fquickly and then went on to refuse to
OL,10,Ftake his medication. It was left as
OL,11,Fhis choice, and his right, not to take
OL,12,Fhis medication and to disengage from
OL,13,Fmental health services.
OL,15,F"Where are the rights of the families?
OL,16,FWhere are the rights of the public if
OL,17,Fin fact it's left to the most
OL,18,Fdisturbed patients to choose not to
OL,19,Fengage in the services?"
OL,21,F'A failure to listen to families'
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
