OL,3,CWhy did the mental health care for
OL,4,Ckiller Valdo Calocane go so wrong?
OL,6,FShe argues that there is a
OL,7,Fmisinterpretation of rights afforded
OL,8,Fto seriously ill people, when there is
OL,9,Fa fundamental lack of resources.
OL,11,FThese include losing half of
OL,12,Fpsychiatric beds since 2000, and a
OL,13,Flack of doctors, community nurses and
OL,14,Fcounsellors. Community teams are so
OL,15,Foverstretched, she says, that they
OL,16,Fcannot follow up on cases like
OL,17,FCalocane.
OL,19,F"But there is another common sense
OL,20,Ffailure - the failure to listen the
OL,21,Ffamilies.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/15
