OL,3,CWhy did the mental health care for
OL,4,Ckiller Valdo Calocane go so wrong?
OL,6,F"His parents were seeking help early
OL,7,Fon and later they were warning about
OL,8,Fthe deterioration in his mental health
OL,9,Fbut none of that was taken into
OL,10,Faccount in the risk assessment.
OL,12,F"This is where we feel it can change.
OL,13,FWe need to make it mandatory that when
OL,14,Ffamilies ring up warning of a
OL,15,Fdeteriorating health state, it must be
OL,16,Fcommunicated to the health teams."
OL,18,F'We need to take each case
OL,19,Findividually'
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/15
